oai_dc:dc.dc:title: LABORATORY STUDY OF RUBBLE FOUNDATIONS FOR VERTICAL BREAKWATERS
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Brebner, A.
Donnelly, P.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: breakwater design
rubble foundation
vertical breakwater
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Laboratory tests have been conducted to determine the stability characteristics of pell-mell placed rubble of sensibly uniform shape and size used as a foundation or as toe protection for the vertical superstructure of a composite breakwater. Data are presented for the design of such breakwater foundations.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 8 (1962): Proceedings of 8th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Mexico City, Mexico, 1962.; 24
